  "text": "Psychopharmacology's guidelines [CITATION_1] , whereas the Canadian Psychiatric Association's guidelines 1 specify that an early response to pharmacotherapy is usually observed in the first 6-8 weeks, but that it may take 12 weeks or longer for pharmacotherapy to exert its full effects in some cases. Since the primary endpoint included patients who had discontinued treatment before the first week of treatment, the efficacy of ESC 10mg was underestimated by including the values imputed by LOCF.",
